<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,468,1938,1965]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,321,1938,1964]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Plagiotrochus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mayr, G." box="[327,468,1939,1965]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref34565" refString="Mayr, G. (1881) Die Genera der gallenbewohnenden Cynipiden. Jahresberichte der Communal-Oberrealschule im I. Bezirke, Wien, 20, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1881">Mayr, 1881</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,2009,2034]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="477" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
The genus is represented by 14 species in the Western Palearctic, of mostly Mediterranean distribution, which induce galls on all parts of oaks from section 
<emphasis box="[694,736,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Ilex</emphasis>
and less commonly 
<emphasis box="[982,1053,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Cerris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nieves-Aldrey, J. L." box="[1072,1309,151,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" pagination="1 - 636" refId="ref35089" refString="Nieves-Aldrey, J. L. (2001) Hymenoptera, Cynipidae. In: Ramos, M. A. (Eds.), Fauna Iberica. Fol. 16. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 636." type="book chapter" year="2001">Nieves-Aldrey 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Abrahamson, W. G." pageId="26" pageNumber="477" pagination="150 - 190" refId="ref34748" refString="Melika, G. &amp; Abrahamson, W. G. (2002) Review of the world genera of oak cynipid wasps (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). In: Melika, G. &amp; Thuroczy, C. (Eds.), Parasitic Wasps: Evolution, Systematics, Biodiversity and Biology Control, Agroinform, Budapest, pp. 150 - 190." type="book chapter" year="2002">Melika &amp; Abrahamson 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Seven species are known in the Eastern Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation author="Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Melika, G." box="[977,1183,188,213]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" pagination="531 - 536" refId="ref36664" refString="Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Melika, G. (2016 b) A new Plagiotrochus Mayr oak gall wasp species from Taiwan (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 19, 531 - 536." type="journal article" year="2016">
Tang 
<emphasis box="[1042,1091,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">et al</emphasis>
. 2016b
</bibRefCitation>
). Both generations are known for most species, the majority of which are associated only with evergreen oaks. Adults resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,257,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Chilaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,257,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Chilaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Three species are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[617,679,260,285]" name="Israel" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Israel</collectingCountry>
on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webb" authorityYear="1838" box="[721,876,260,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calliprinos">
<emphasis box="[721,876,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Q. calliprinos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one of which has been found only once.
</paragraph>
